From ac1f68d77e00b13ceed46cf531d5b7f811da034a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Zach Taylor <zctaylor.work@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 13:03:05 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 06/48] Add configurable, selectable server/agent backends

New crate::util::agent_backends: an agent_backends.toml (in Warp's config dir)
defining alternative backends (id/name/server_url/ws_url) plus a 'selected' id.
apply_selected_backend() overrides ChannelState's server + websocket URLs at
startup (wired into lib.rs::run before the dev-only CLI override gate, applied
unconditionally). The built-in Warp backend is always available and is the
default when nothing is selected.
---
